main event: A visual observation of a single oval object reported on March 6, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of about 10,000 feet.,The angular velocity of the object was about 1 degree per second.,The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute.,No photographs were taken or available.,The incident was part of Project Blue Book, an official investigation into UFO sightings.
sighted object: one oval object in the sky
